<br>
I chose Saracen because I wanted to dual wield thrust weapons and have access to Dragonfang. I know I know, I knew going into it that Dragonfang wouldn't be viable...but I don't think thats fair. I think Saracen Mercenaries speccing thrust should become just as viable as those Slash Briton and Highlander mercenaries when it comes to using their weapon skill. <br>
<br>
This is in no way a complaint..I love my mercenary more than I expected I would. It's a pure positional and reactionary fighter. However, we're totally dependent upon Dual Wielding because Thrust is useless to us. Once in a blue moon, literally, I'll both evade and successfully land Dragonfang. For me Dragonfang doesn't deal quite as much damage as Dual Shadows, the stun effect is nice and allows me around three to four extra attacks. <br>
<br>
The point of all this rambling? I think Mercenaries should have atleast Evade II. I've read over this forum, I've seen the arguements against Evade II and why we'll never get it, we're too defensive and etc...but..Not everyone plays a Highlander or even a Briton. I'm play a Saracen Mercenary, my con is low by default and raises only tetriary. I drop faster than any other tank and light tank I'm grouped with which is expected, even with +hits and +con maxed in my template. Ontop of that when going toe-to-toe with another tank class, I can only use Dual Shadows which warrants a defense penalty I can't afford as a Saracen Mercenary. While Highlander and Briton Slash Mercenaries are able to use their Slash anytimes. Yes I know Light Tanks are meant to assist and not go toe-to-toe with tanks, but sometimes you can't avoid it..in RvR you're usually snared and can't avoid such confrontations.<br>
<br>
Really, what defense do we have? We have extra absorb on our armor, thats ALL. Yes we have Evade I and Advanced Evade, but with most mercs high parry checks and the ridiculously low chance to evade, would you miss having Evade I and Advanced Evade all that much?<br>
<br>
I don't get heavily involved into the mathematics behind the game, and how often something should happen and etc. All I know is that in RvR, I as a Saracen Mercenary lack in defense, where Highlander and Briton Slash mercenaries lack in defense they make up in damage and versatility, being able to use Amy Slash and Diamond Slash along with their Dual Wielding styles.<br>
<br>
Purchase Dodger? Really, I tried, even with Augumented Dexterity II, Augumented Quickness II, Dodger II, 200 Dexterity (including Aug Dex II), 157 Quickness (including Aug Qui II). I still evaded once every blue moon. I even took away MoParrying and the +parry from my SC template to lower my chance to parry and hopefully let my evade check more.<br>
<br>
Even if Evade II is out of the question which I don't think it is. There has to be some way to make Thrust viable for Saracen Mercenaries, maybe make Dex and Qui modify the Evade chance more for mercenaries than other classes? It'd increase a thrust Saracen's efficiency while not overpowering Highlander and Briton mercs. <br>
<br>
Just some finishing notes, this post is about making Saracen Thrust Mercenaries more viable. I'm not looking for options on how to make my mercenary better, such as respec to Dodger 5 or respec to Slash. I want to see my spec as viable and as efficient as any other Mercenary spec. I think this can be done through either a thrust style revision from mercenaries or simply raising our evade chance through some method. Also, again, I'm very satisfied with my merc, I just noticed I underperform in areas where I feel I should be equal with the other merc specs. If you agree with me your highness Team Lead (no sarcasm I'm thankful you do this), I hope you could come up with some better ideas than me to suggest. <br>
<br>
I'm new to these boards so take it easy on me if anyone is tired of giving the same response to people like me. This isn't a &quot;please give Evade II&quot; post, I'm just wondering if anyone feels the same about me in regards to Saracen Thrust Mercenaries and their performance compared to other merc specs and other light tanks in general.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirala>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mercenary Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 714<br> <font color=#000000>(10/12/03 10:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=87.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Saracen Mercenaries</span><hr size=1> Okay, first off, Evade is checked <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>before</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Parry, so lowering your Parry is a BAD move.  As a Saracen your MUCH higher Dex will improve your defense substantially (especially when buffed) so that it balances out the lower Con (ideally anyway).<br>
<br>
I'm Saracen as well (and since this was my very first character, I don't think I even optimised my starting stats...).  While we do tend to miss out on some Weaponskill due to low Str (though Thrust spec does even it out, ya got a bonus there), I think our increased defense tends to balance things.  I personally don't feel that we're lacking anything as a race, especially since we have the option to raise stats through RA's.<br>
